== Congressional certification ==
During the joint session of Congress to count the electoral votes, a dispute occurred over Wisconsin&#x27;s slate. The electors of Wisconsin, delayed by a snowstorm, did not cast their votes for Frémont and Dayton until several days after the appointed time and sent a certificate mentioning this fact. When the votes for the state were opened by acting Vice President James Mason, he counted them over the objections of the leadership of both Houses of Congress.

